-- Turkey Will Invite Bids for Hamitabat Power Plant Tomorrow
-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 2012-08-09T14:41:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/turkey-will-invite-bids-for-hamitabat-power-plant-tomorrow-1-.html
Turkey ’s asset sales agency will
invite bids for the 1,120-megawatt Hamitabat natural gas-fired
power plant tomorrow.  The Privatization Administration  will also put the Ankara
natural gas grid up for sale “within a few weeks,” Ahmet Aksu,
head of the agency, said in an interview in the city.  The Ankara-based agency set a deadline of Oct. 19 for
bidding on the Hamitabat plant, according to an agency document
seen by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
